  "title": "Energy changes in system",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><include href=\"../Passage/VH967196.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A small particle with a charge of magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"q\"><math alttext=\"q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>q</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is released from rest at point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>B</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and moves until it hits point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>A</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. If the potential difference <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"delta V\"><math alttext=\"delta V\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> between the plates is known, which of the following correctly explains a method to determine the increase in kinetic energy of the particle?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i1",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Use <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"q delta V\"><math alttext=\"q delta V\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>q</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> to determine the decrease in the potential energy of the plates-particle system. That is equal to the increase in the kinetic energy of the particle.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Use <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction q delta V, over d\"><math alttext=\"the fraction q delta V, over d\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mstyle><mrow><mi>q</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></math></span></span> to determine the decrease in the potential energy of the plates-particle system. That is equal to the increase in the kinetic energy of the particle.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Use <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"q delta V\"><math alttext=\"q delta V\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>q</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> to determine the work done by an external force on the plates-particle system. That is equal to the increase in the kinetic energy of the particle.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Use <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction q delta V, over d \"><math alttext=\"the fraction q delta V, over d \" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mstyle><mrow><mi>q</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></math></span></span> to determine the work done by an external force on the plates-particle system. That is equal to the increase in the kinetic energy of the particle.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
    ]
